Package JourneyPlanner

Class RoutingStation

  • java.lang.Object
    • JourneyPlanner.Station
      • JourneyPlanner.RoutingStation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<RoutingStation>
    public class RoutingStation
extends Station
implements java.lang.Comparable<RoutingStation>
    A RoutingStation object is a Station object with all the variables needed for Dijkstra's algorithm in the getRoute methods of the Route class, e.g. cost, prev = previous station visited in the shortest path
    Author:
    Zac Schmidt, Michael Wade
    See Also:
    Station, Route

      The train number of the train taken to get to this station on the shortest path

    • Constructor Detail

      • RoutingStation

        public RoutingStation​(Station station)
        Creates a RoutingStation object extended from a non-null Station object. Name and adjacentStations (from Station) are given with pass-by-reference. The variables of RoutingStation are initialised to the default values cost = Time.MAX_TIME, prev = null, timeArrivedAt = Time.MAX_TIME, prevTrain = 0, prevLine = null, popped = false
        Parameters:
        station - the corresponding Station object
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if station is null
